post_text: Don't miss this event - EMPTY BOWLS DINNER!! Tonight, March 4th, from 5-7 PM, at Bumps at the base of Buttermilk. Aspen Middle School, Aspen Community School and Aspen Country Day students have created hundreds of beautiful ceramic bowls for an Empty Bowls dinner where the community is invited to a simple meal of soup, bread and dessert. In exchange for a meal and a bowl (to keep), guests are asked to give a $10 dollar donation. All money raised benefits Lift Up!

post_text:
New superintendent. New facilities and buildings plan. Outdoor Education and Experiential Education. Academic excellence. College prep and real-world readiness. College admission. Test scores. Athletics. Life Skills. Social/emotional learning and well-being. Teamwork. Internships and apprenticeships. Outstanding teachers. Parent involvement. There are a lot of pieces to the puzzle of providing education and the perfect upbringing for our youth.

"It takes a village," as they say. ASD is in the process of creating a strategic plan - a document that will guide and clarify decision making processes for years to come. We would love for YOU to join us in this planning process and provide your feedback! Hope we see you tonight at 5pm in the AHS Commons.

post_text:
Did You Know That...
Last June, the Aspen School District began the process of developing a strategic plan. It all started with 30+ district employees, coming together to imagine the future of education for our students. Throughout the development of this plan, and as a result of it, we desire to nurture a culture of collaboration and trust.

Creating this plan is a TEAM effort. When all is said and done, the plan should reflect the combined voices of all involved parties: teachers, students, parents, community members.

In case you've missed one of the earlier collaborative efforts, January 29th is your night! Get up to speed on the work done so far and have a say in Aspen School District's future. See you there?

We are truly overwhelmed with gratitude and know our graduates are going to experience one of the most magical evening of their lives, thanks to everyone‚Äôs support and generosity. Honoring our graduates like this is the best way to end their days at Aspen High School on the highest note, and you have all made this possible. Thank you for being a part of our Project Graduation Village!

With heartfelt gratitude,

Team Project Graduation

post_text:
AMS PARENTS & COMMUNITY - Please join us at Aspen Middle School on Monday, May 20 from 4-5pm in the AMS Library to share some thinking about how we can work together to strengthen the academic and behavior supports for all students at Aspen Middle School.

This dialog and work session will be led from representatives of the SWIFT Education Center. SWIFT Schools is committed to equity based inclusion, where every child is valued and given the supports that he or she needs to succeed.

We hope that you can join us in this first of many conversations about how we can support Aspen Middle School students.

Best Regards,
The Middle School SWIFT Team

SWEET SOUNDS | The AMS Band had 15 students audition and be accepted into the Northwest Colorado Music Educators Honor Band that took place at Summit Middle School in Frisco. For two days the students rehearsed with over 80 other students in 6th, 7th, 8th grade representing 16 middle schools throughout the western slope. The event concluded with a spectacular concert of 6 pieces of music played by the honor band students.

content and photo credit: Andy Farmer

A live-streamed and recorded event will occur with two conversations providing stories, tools, coping mechanisms and resources for young adults ages 13+, parents, teachers, and all of our communities.

There will be a Spanish interpreter and tickets are free for teachers, health professionals, families in need, and students 13-21 (under 13 not recommended). post_text:
SOPHOMORE AND JUNIOR PARENTS - Have you registered yet for our College Application Case Study Program? By attending this program, you will gain valuable insight into the application review process. We have 32 college representatives who will be walking you through the application review process. You will learn about how they interpret the information on the application. The evening will conclude with a brief, college mini-fair. We hope that you will join us for an enjoyable and informative evening as we take a step closer to college.

When: April 17th, from 5:15 pm-8:30 pm
Where: Check-in at the District Theater, mini-fair in the High School Commons
Who: This event is geared towards our sophomores, juniors, and their parents

Thanks and we cannot wait to see you on the 17th!
Register here: http://bit.ly/2UsuJuD

video and content credit: Charlie Laube and Melissa Lustig of the Aspen High School College Counseling Office

post_text: Please join us Monday, April 8 from 8:30-9:30am for a Superintendent's Coffee in the ASD Board Room. We're excited to introduce our newest communication feature, the ASD App. We'll demonstrate how it works and review all the ASD and BOE communications channels and which ones may be right for you. We will also discuss some new ways that parents can get involved with the District, including VolunteerMatch. We hope to see you there!

Hats off to Rae Lampe, Hilary Forsyth (ACS) and Paula Ponto (ACD) for a hugely successful EMPTY BOWLS 2019!

Wednesday, March 6th, 2019 over 500 + people from our community gathered at Bumps at the base of Buttermilk to share a simple meal of delicious soup, fresh bread, and yummy desserts. Guests chose a bowl from over 450 hundred beautiful ceramic bowls that were handmade by students at the Aspen Middle School, the Aspen Community School and the Aspen Country Day School, for their soup and to take home as a reminder that there are always empty bowls in the world. (read more on our blog post below)
